    <p><b>Economic:</b> While the researchers are working out what to do with the food ideas they have, we’re going to try and build up the little camp area to something that will house these refugees a little more comfortably.  Probably repurpose a few of the unused smaller buildings from the actual town for supplies.</p>
    <p><i>Investment</i> trapping of <b>Infrastructure</b></p>
    <p>1 advantage, 3 successes, 0 triumphs</p>
    <p><b>Political:</b> Well then that was exciting.  Upon finding out that Fuzzy had in fact been in Trischal’s office the whole time, everyone agrees that what happened was the best outcome possible.  Going forward, it’s probably a good idea to have descriptions of elves like that on a rather permanente watch list.  Based on what Shyrendora knows from her brief conversation with Dust at the potluck, others might be having similar issues.  She intends to send some messages to the dreamdust elves to see if Dust has any more information that he can lend on these new elves.  For now however, they are going to try and keep up their routine that they are getting into.  If it continues to do well enough, there are talks of making a unit/division of spyhunters for the Hilt’Inn specifically.</p>
    <p><i>Cloak and Dagger</i> trapping of <b>Spycraft</b></p>
    <p>0 advantages, 4 successes, 0 triumphs</p>
    <p><b>Military: </b>Scouting further into caverns so we know what else is around us aside from the Hilt’Inn and the collapsed warren.  We know that there is much more going into the caldera, but we want to be cautious of potential straggler skeletons as well as any more excessive amount of traps.  (Cautious = maybe 2 squares connected to the caverns)  If this goes decently, Trischal has agreed that a small group could possibly go visit the winged-elves later on to see what those caves they have are all about, plus give some pointers on stone work if they still need it.</p>
    <p><i>Pathfinders</i> trapping of <b>Reconnaissance</b> </p>
    <p>Stunnnttt don’t forget stunttttt you dumb dumb</p>
    <p>3 advantages, 1 success, 0 triumphs</p>
    <p><b>Mental:</b> Based on what we witnessed with the blade elves and their food problems, we’re going to try and research what we could put out at the camp as a potential small farm for the refugees.  Something easy enough for them to take care of with a little guidance or gather food for themselves before they move onwards kind of thing.  In theory they want to make something that can work for the current situation, but also something that could be utilized in the future when the refugee influx has calmed down.  (It’s probably potatoes but we’ll see what fate gives us)</p>
    <p><i>Research</i> trapping of <b>Academics</b></p>
